<p>Went with Beard for a day trip to Lake Wallace in the Blue Mountains.
It was a rainy day but fortunately not too windy.</p>

<!-- more -->

<h2 id="fishing">Fishing</h2>
<p>I started spinning with a Celta lure in the brown trout pattern.</p>
<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6457.jpeg">
  <img src="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6457.jpeg" alt="" />
  
    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>The first rainbow trout took my lure very deep
down its mouth (and I left my pliers in the car) so decided to keep
it.<br />
The next came on the following cast, and shortly after I caught
a third, smaller one which was let go. After 15 minutes of action,
the wind changed direction and not much else happened that afternoon.</p>
<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6435.jpeg">
  <img src="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6435.jpeg" alt="" />
  
    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>I also had a good chat with an arborist who was locking one of the gates. He, along
with other volunteers, were planting trees along the lake shore.</p>

<p>Beard casting near the dam wall.</p>
<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6443.jpeg">
