<h2 id="smoked-rainbow-trout">Smoked Rainbow Trout</h2>
<p>It was only the next day, while preparing the fish, that I noticed both were
tagged (sometimes, Iâ€™m not very observant). These were reported to the 
<a href="https://www.dpi.nsw.gov.au/fishing/recreational/resources/fish-tagging/recapture-form">Department of Primary Industries Tagging Program</a>. One was 30cm and the 
other 31cm.</p>
<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6453.jpeg">
  <img src="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6453.jpeg" alt="" />
  
    <figcaption>
      

    </figcaption></a></figure>

<p>Dried the fish and covered them with salt, including the cavity. On the bottom
of a foil-lined wok I added: 1/2 cup rice, 5 tablespoons of tea and 6 bay leaves.</p>
<figure class="">
  <a href="/assets/images/2020/08/IMG_6458.jpg">
